KwaZulu-Natal's Richmond Council municipal manager, Sibusiso Sithole, was shot and killed by unknown suspects on Monday.The African National Congress (ANC) in KZN described Sithole as one of the best municipal managers in the province, while the Democratic Alliance (DA) said he was killed because he was trying to root out corruption in the municipality. 702 breakfast host Xolani Gwala strongly condemns the killing.Listen to the full comment below...